The paper discusses the field of multi-agent systems (MAS) within artificial intelligence, which is a subfield of AI (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on Distributed Constraint Optimization Problems (DCOPs), which are a prominent agent model in MAS. Therefore, the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.MA (multi-agent systems) and cs.DC (distributed computing). The paper also discusses resolution methods and applications, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
